          <h3 class="text-center" id="pg1"> Guestbook</h3>
          <br>
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
            <h4>Description</h4>
            <p>
              The MAZI Guestbook is an open source application that can used in events enabling the audience to share their thoughts, photos, etc.
            </p>
            
            <h4>Administration Guide</h4>
            <p>
              To moderate the content, you go to <b><a target="_blank" href="http://portal.mazizone.eu:8081/#admin" class="app-link" >local.mazizone.eu:8081/#admin</a></b></br> (username: <b>admin</b> password: <b>mazizone</b>), where you can delete any submission that is inappropriate.
            </p>

            <h4>Alternative views of content</h4>
            <p>
              As well as standard web browser presentation of content, GuestBook supports two other views of content
            </p>
            <p><b>Slideshow view:</b> <a href="http://portal.mazizone.eu:8081/#projection" target='_blank'>http://portal.mazizone.eu:8081/#projection</a> *</p>
            <p><b>Tablet view:</b> <a href="http://portal.mazizone.eu:8081/#tablet" target='_blank'>http://portal.mazizone.eu:8081/#tablet</a> *</p>
            <p>* all links work when you are connected to your MAZI Zone.</p>

            <h4>Tags</h4>
            <p>
              When contributing a post, users are offered predefined tag boxes to select to give profile information. These can be edited by the administrator. In order to change tags, open the config.js file, which is held here: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/config.js</b> You can remove or edit a tag as you wish in this code line
            </p>
            <pre><code>
              $tags: ['Tag1', 'Tag2', 'Tag3', 'Tag4']
            </code></pre>

            <h4>Background Image</h4>
            <p>
              In order to change the background image, save the image you want in the following path: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/images</b> Replace the DSI.jpg of the following code, with the name of your image. You can find the code in the following path: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/templates/header_tmpl.html</b>
            </p>
            <pre><code>
              &ltdiv class="header-bar"&gt&lt/div&gt
              &ltdiv class="header-image column"&gt&ltimg src="images/DSI.jpg"&gt&lt/div&gt
            </code></pre>
            <p>
              Alternatively, you could just replace the file "header-img.png" with the new image file. If you have a hybrid letterbox, in the same folder you can also replace the "logo" image by replacing the file "logo.png" in the same repository.
            </p>

            <h4>Appearance and input</h4>
            <p>
              You can further modify the appearance of the GuestBook manually by editing the various templates here: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/templates/</b>
            </p>

            <h4>Admin Password</h4>
            <p>
              In order to change the admin password, open the config.js file ,which takes place in this path: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/node/config.js</b>, and then fill the authPassword with the password you like.
            </p>
            <pre><code>
              /* AUTH DATA */
              authName: 'admin',
              authPassword: 'password',
            </code></pre>

            <h4>Message</h4>
            <p>
              In order to change the message, open the submission_input_tmpl.html file , which takes place in this path: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/templates/</b>submission_input_tmpl.html, and then change the message (i.e., "Click here to join the Guestbook" ...) with the message you wish to be displayed.
            </p>

            <h4>Setting upload size of files and formats</h4>
            <p>
              To customise the file upload size and file formats allowed, edit the following file:</br>
              <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/node/config.js</b>
            </p>
            <p>
              By default, the maximum file upload size is 1024 x 1024 x 2 bytes (2 Mb). The following file types are allowed: 'image/jpg','image/jpeg','image/png','image/gif'
            </p>

            <h4>Changing font colours</h4>
            <p>
              The main css is available at: <b>/var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/css/</b>
            </p>
            
            <h4>Saving the content of a MAZI Zone deployment</h4>
            <p>
              If you want to record the input of a specific MAZI Zone deployment for future use or archiving, and until the corresponding admin function is properly implemented, you can copy the folder "/var/files/" to another folder (e.g., "cp -r ./files files_[date]_[place]"). This new folder can be compressed and transferred to a local storage.
            </p>
